{{Infobox company | name = Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship | industry = [[Mixed martial arts]] | location_city = [[Dallas]], [[Texas]] | location_country = U.S. }}
'''Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship''' (''Art of War'') is a defunct U.S.-based Mixed martial arts (MMA) organization. The Art of War was headquartered in Dallas, Texas and was owned and operated by SUN Sports & Entertainment, Inc. It is not related to Chinese MMA promotion [[Art of War Fighting Championship]].
== History ==
The Art of War held six events.
The first event, Art of War 1<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/events/AOW-Art-of-War-1-4873|title=AOW - Art of War 1|last=Sherdog.com|website=Sherdog|access-date=2018-02-19}}</ref>, was on March 9, 2007 at the American Airlines Center in front of over 6,000 attendees. The headliner was [[Pedro Rizzo]] vs [[Justin Eilers]]. The fight aired on HDNET.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmaweekly.com/rizzo-defeats-eilers-on-art-of-war-show-2|title=– RIZZO DEFEATS EILERS ON "ART OF WAR" SHOW {{!}} MMAWeekly.com|website=www.mmaweekly.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-19}}</ref>
Art of War 2<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/events/AOW-Art-of-War-2-5192|title=AOW - Art of War 2|last=Sherdog.com|website=Sherdog|access-date=2018-02-19}}</ref> took place May 11, 2007 in Austin, Texas.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.austinchronicle.com/daily/sports/2007-05-13/474543/|title=Guillen Defeats Sims in Art of War 2’s No. 1 Stunner (Wh-What, Wh-What, What?)|access-date=2018-02-19|language=en-US}}</ref> The headliner was Chris Guillen vs [[Wes Sims (fighter)|Wes Sims]].
The first pay-per-view Art of War 3<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/events/AOW-Art-of-War-3-5285|title=AOW - Art of War 3|last=Sherdog.com|website=Sherdog|access-date=2018-02-19}}</ref> took place on September 1, 2007 at American Airlines Center in Dallas, Texas<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/pressreleases/MonsonRizzo-Headline-Art-of-War-8695|title=Monson-Rizzo Headline Art of War|last=Sherdog.com|website=Sherdog|access-date=2018-02-19}}</ref>. The main event featured former UFC fighters [[Jeff Monson]] and [[Pedro Rizzo]]. The fight was distributed by [[American Television Distribution]] and aired on [[Dish Network]].
