__NOTOC__
The '''girl next door''' is a [[Girl|young female]] [[stock character]] who is described as "sweet, ordinary and caring" and lives right next door. They are often used in [[Romance novel|romantic stories]], where the hero is caught in a [[love triangle]] between two women and will usually choose the "girl next door" he grew up with, rather than a more well-off or beautiful woman with less morals.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/829154479|title=Ebert's bigger little movie glossary : a greatly expanded and much improved compendium of movie clichés, stereotypes, obligatory scenes, hackneyed formulas, shopworn conventions, and outdated archetypes|date=1999|publisher=Andrews McMeel|others=Ebert, Roger.|isbn=0740792466|location=Kansas City, Mo.|oclc=829154479}}</ref> Other times, this character ignores the hero for another male character, despite being the object of his affections.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/987796701|title=Romancing the zombie : essays on the undead as significant "other"|last=|first=|publisher=|others=Szanter, Ashley,, Richards, Jessica K.,, Bishop, Kyle William, 1973-|year=|isbn=147666742X|location=Jefferson, North Carolina|pages=45|oclc=987796701}}</ref>{{bettersource|date=July 2018}}

The [[Boy|masculine]] counterpart is '''boy next door''', who is also described as "wholesome, sweet and shy".{{cn|date=July 2018}}

