{{Infobox Theatre |name = River Run Centre |image = River Run Centre in Guelph ON.jpg |caption = |address = |city = [[Guelph]], [[Ontario]] |designation = |latitude = |longitude = |architect = |owner = |capacity = |type = [[Performing arts center|performing arts centre]] |opened = October 4, 1997 |yearsactive = 1997-present |rebuilt = |closed = |othernames = |production = |currentuse = Professional and amateur theatre |website = http://riverrun.ca/ Official site }}
The '''River Run Centre''' is a [[Performing arts center|performing arts centre]] in [[Guelph]], [[Ontario]], Canada.
Construction of the facility began in 1995 and cost $15 million.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://riverrun.ca/about/index.cfm?itemID=41|title= River Run Centre: The Beginnings|accessdate= 2009-03-08|publisher= River Run Centre official site|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20091127152919/http://riverrun.ca/about/index.cfm?itemID=41|archivedate= 2009-11-27|df= }}</ref> It officially opened on October 4, 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://riverrun.ca/about/index.cfm?itemID=42|title= River Run Centre: The Official Opening|accessdate= 2009-03-08|publisher= River Run Centre official site|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20091127152606/http://riverrun.ca/about/index.cfm?itemID=42|archivedate= 2009-11-27|df= }}</ref>
The facility has three halls:
*The Main Hall, which can seat 785 *The Co-operators Hall, which seats 225 *The Canada Company Hall
